               Asperula oligantha is mentioned by Miquel;

Miquel (1856), p. 16.
                I use the name as a collective one of all of Dr Hooker's Australian species, none of his appellations being legitimate for the one species as comprehended by me.

Your views of genera, as artificial, I share fully That D.C.
De Candolle. & others should in transferring species to other genera to which they have been drawn by others before always fall back upon that specific name first adopted by some author can not establish a law;
See G. Bentham to M, 24 November 1864. one's own feelings must dictate what is right & wrong & mine teach me that such a proceeding is most inequitable.
